Hive Practical questions:-

1. Hive Join operations

Create a  table named CUSTOMERS(ID | NAME | AGE | ADDRESS   | SALARY)
Create a Second  table ORDER(OID | DATE | CUSTOMER_ID | AMOUNT

Now perform different joins operations on top of these tables
(Inner JOIN, LEFT OUTER JOIN ,RIGHT OUTER JOIN ,FULL OUTER JOIN)

Ans :- Wright a data in vim editor and store in hdfs,
create a customer table :-
     create table if not exists customer_data
     (
     id int,
     name string,
     age int,
     address string,
     salary int
     )
     row format delimited
     fields terminated by ',';
     
now load a data in hdfs :-
load data inpath '/tmp/hive_data/customer_data.csv' into table customer_data;

create order table :-
     create table if not exists order_data_v1
     (
     oid int,
     date_id string,
     customer_id int,
     amount int
     )
     row format delimited
     fields terminated by ',';
load data :-
 load data inpath '/tmp/hive_data/order.csv' into table order_data_v1;

Now perfon join querys :-
     select
     c.id,
     c.name,
     c.age,
     o.amount
     from customer_data c join order_data_v1 o
     on (c.id = o.customer_id);
result :-
c.id    c.name  c.age   o.amount
1       sumit   19      20
2       Aadi    6       25
3       Sangeet 20      30
4       Ajay    22      35

Now left outer join query :-
     select
     c.id,
     c.name,
     o.amount,
     o.date_id
     from customer_data c
     left outer join order_data_v1 o
     on (c.id = o.customer_id);
result:-
c.id    c.name  o.amount        o.date_id
1       sumit   20      01-09-2022
2       Aadi    25      02-09-2022
3       Sangeet 30      03-09-2022
4       Ajay    35      04-09-2022

